her&s;elf upon the victory &s;he had obtained; and
thinking it unnece&s;&s;ary to continue the re&s;erve
&s;he had hitherto indu&s;triou&s;ly affected, re&s;olved
from that day to &s;weeten her behaviour towards
him with &s;uch a da&s;h of affection, as could not
