<P>Having no inclination to &s;leep, her thoughts
during the remaining part of the night were en|gr$&s;&s;ed
by a &s;cheme of reformation &s;he was re|$$ved
to execute in the family; and no &s;ooner
did the fir&s;t lark bid &s;alutation to the morn, than
$tarting from her humble couch, and huddling on
her cloaths, &s;he &s;allied from her chamber, ex|plored
her way thro' paths before unknown, and
in the cour&s;e of her re&s;earches perceived a large
bell, to which &s;he made &s;uch effectual application
as alarmed every &s;oul in the family. In a mo|ment
&s;he was &s;urrounded by Hatchway, Pipes,
and all the re&s;t of the &s;ervants half dre&s;&s;ed; but
&s;eeing none of the feminine gender appear, &s;he
began to &s;torm at the &s;loth and lazine&s;s of the
maids, who, &s;he ob&s;erved, ought to have been
