<P>This hope helped to con&s;ole him under the ex|traordinary
expence to which he was expo&s;ed by
the profu&s;ion of his wife, e&s;pecially when he con|&s;idered
that his compliance with her prodigality
would be limited to the expiration of the nine
months, of which the be&s;t part was by this time
elap&s;ed; yet in &s;pite of all this philo&s;ophical re|&s;ignation,
her fancy &s;ometimes &s;oared to &s;uch a
ridiculous and intolerable pitch of in&s;olence and
ab&s;urdity, that his temper for&s;ook him, and he
could not help wi&s;hing in &s;ecret, that her pride
