&s;he was confirmed in this caution by her mo|ther,
who very wi&s;ely, in her civilities to him,
maintained a &s;ort of ceremonious di&s;tance, which
&s;he thought not only requi&s;ite for the honour and
intere&s;t of her family, but likewi&s;e for her own
