<P>The nature of this adventure being unknown
to all except tho&s;e who could be depended upon,
every body who inquired about the cau&s;e of Pe|regrine's
ab&s;ence, was told that he had been with
a relation in the country, and the ma&s;ter conde|&s;cended
to overlook his indi&s;cretion; &s;o that
Hatchway &s;eeing every thing &s;ettled to the &s;ati&s;|faction
of his friend, returned to the garri&s;on,
