in con&s;equence of Mr. Pickle's repeated caution.
While the old gentlewoman turned to a &s;ervant,
in order to give directions about the di&s;po&s;al of
this pre&s;ent, Pipes looked upon this as a favour|able
occa&s;ion to tran&s;act his bu&s;ine&s;s with Emilia,
and therefore, &s;hutting one eye, with a jirk of his
<PB N="163" REF="171">
thumb towards his left &s;houlder, and a mo&s;t &s;ig|nificant
twi&s;t of his countenance, he beckoned
the young lady into another room, as if he had
been fraught with&s;omething of con&s;equences, which
